// Sprint 1 acceptance fixture: malformed top-level declaration.
// The middle `fn` is followed immediately by a newline rather than a
// function name — the parser cannot build an FnDecl. It must produce
// an ErrorDecl at that position, synchronise on the next top-level
// keyword (the following `fn`), and parse the declarations on either
// side cleanly. Exactly one diagnostic is emitted.
fn first(): Int { return 1 }

fn
fn last(): Int { return 99 }
